PHASE 1 – AUTONOMOUS CURATION (STRATEGY)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Analyze [BRAND NAME] autonomously.

1. Identify:
- the brand’s industry
- its core physical product
  (examples:
   sports brand → balls / equipment
   food brand → packaging / boxes
   finance brand → metal cards
   lifestyle brand → signature objects)

2. Define the color strategy:

Background Color:
- A deep, rich, textured tone derived from the brand’s secondary palette
- Examples: deep teal, navy, burgundy, slate grey
- Must feel premium, moody, editorial

Merch Color:
- A contrasting warm or neutral tone
- Examples: camel, cream, muted orange, off-white
- Must pop clearly against the background

3. Select the Merch Item:
Choose ONE high-quality apparel item that fits the brand’s vibe:
- Varsity letterman jacket
- Heavyweight hoodie
- Structured canvas tote
- Wool scarf or knit
The item must feel:
- expensive
- tactile
- collectible

